modules.description: This module provides tools for structured version tracking and changelog generation, supporting operations like parsing versioned releases with dates and categories, serializing contributor data, and comparing semantic versions using custom operators. It works with hierarchical data models representing releases, entries, and contributor lists, along with utilities for extracting version metadata via regex patterns. Typical use cases include converting JSON-formatted changelog data into typed structures, generating human-readable release notes, and automating version bump detection in development workflows.
